>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
Actual perameter and formal peramet

->formal perameter pass in function defination time
->actual pearmeter pass at function calling time
  e.g
  void sum(int a,int b) //formal perameter
  {
    int ans;
    ans=a+b;
  }
  void main()
  {
    int a=10,b=20;
    sum(a,b);  //actual perameter
  }
=========================================================================================================
 -> call by value:callby value is a most powerfull concept of function and pointer topic
  it dose not change actual parameter if we appply any cahnge in formal perameter in call
  value we just passing copy of value not actual perameter
  {matlab hum agr forml perameter(user difien) me chan kare or vo actule perameter me farak na pade uko hum call by value bolenge}

  e.g
  void swipe(int a,int b)//formal perameter
  {
    int ans;
          ans=a;
          a=b;
          b=ans;
  }
  void main()
  {
    int a=10,b=20;//actual perameter
    printf("\nbefor change");
    printf("\na=%d and b=%d",a,b);
    swipe(a,b);//call by value
    printf("\nafter change");
    printf("\na=%d and b=%d",a,b);
  }
  output:
  befor change
  a=10 and b=20
  after change
  a=10 and b=20
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
->call by reference:when we pass actual perameter in function calling time and apply changes in formal 
perameter it direct affect actual perameter

because inside of pussing copy of value here we are passing adress of actual perameters.

e.g
  void swipe(int *a,int *b)  formal perameter
  {
    int ans;
          ans=*a;
          *a=*b;
          *b=ans;
  }
  void main()
  {
    int a=10,b=20;//actual perameter
    printf("\nbefor change");
    printf("\na=%d and b=%d",a,b);
    swipe(&a,&b);//call by reference
    printf("\nafter change");
    printf("\na=%d and b=%d",a,b);
  }
  output:
  befor change
  a=10 and b=20
  after change
  a=20 and b=10